      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLUFFY'S GIRL (2) is fast and went close at Launceston before just missing here this grade. Draws to advantage and has a handy 2kg claim. She can go one better. ZUNI (4) was quickly back on track, beaten a half-length at Launceston. She has more up her sleeve and has placed on this surface. PLATINUM REGGAE (5) resumes in the same race and finished a head behind the above. She's further improved and has a strong record this course/trip. The awkward barrier is a niggle. MISS KEEDS (3) will use the rail and here form this course and over the distance is hard to fault. She's an include at a price. VOLKANOVSKI (6) gets in well with the 3kg claim and is in the mix.",
